abstract: Iraqi security forces use variety of means, including live ammunition, to quell anti-government protest in Green Zone, Baghdad central district where Parliament is located; at least four demonstrators are killed and 90 injured, raising concerns incident will fuel spread of Islamic State ideology in country.
lead_paragraph: The United Nations warned that a sweep by security forces could hamper the fight against the Islamic State, while some termed the government’s response as excessive.

headline.main: Protests in Baghdad’s Green Zone Leave 4 Dead and 90 Injured
headline.print_headline: Iraqis Kill 4 at Protest Breaching Green Zone
